summary.text: Observed Holiday: Trash collection cancelled & not rescheduled

description.text:
This is an observed holiday.

Trash collection for this holiday has been cancelled and is not being rescheduled. Instead residents are permitted to place out double the amount of cans or bags of household trash on their next scheduled trash collection day. The maximum amount of household trash for a single family home is 12 cans or bags each weighing 50 lbs. or less on a double collection day.

contact.text: Department of Environmental Waste Management; 631-351-3186; EWM@HuntingtonNY.gov; HuntingtonNY.gov/trash

description.text:
Rinse plastic, glass and metal recyclables clean and put into your dedicated recycling container that is stickered on both sides with “Huntington Recycles” decals. The container, when full, should be no more than 50 lbs. Lids and caps are recyclable but should be removed before placing in recycling container. Place your covered recycling container curbside on days indicated by this calendar. Recycling should not be put out in plastic bags, it should be loose in your recycling container.

Acceptable Glass, Metal and Plastic Recyclables Include:

  • Food and beverage cans
  • Plastic food & beverage containers
  • Unsoiled disposable aluminum pans & aluminum foil
  • Wine beverage, liquor and juice bottles
  • Food jars
  • Shampoo and detergent bottles
  • All plastic food, soap & beverage containers with Resin Codes 1 – 7 are accepted.

Do Not Put these Contaminants In Your Recycling Bin:

  • Plastic bags and plastic wrap
  • Plastic toys
  • Hangers
  • Aerosol cans
  • Flower pots & plant containers
  • Ceramic items
  • Oil cans
  • Light bulbs
  • Mirrors and plate glass
  • Durable cookware & Tupperware
  • Empty paint cans
  • Plastic items without a resin code symbol.

Additional Recycling Information:

  • “Back To Basics” dual stream recycling collection
  • Recycling containers and decals
  • Recycling contamination or “when in doubt throw it out”

contact.text: Department of Environmental Waste Management; 631-351-3186; EWM@HuntingtonNY.gov; HuntingtonNY.gov/http://www.huntingtonny.gov/BottlesCansPlasticsRecycling

description.text: Residents on this collection route are permitted to place out double the amount of cans or bags of household trash due to the observed holiday on their prior collection day.  The maximum amount for a single family home is 12 cans or bags on a double collection day.

Junk mail, newspapers and magazines are recyclable. To put out for collection the paper recycling can be: tied into bundles no more than 12” high, put in paper grocery bags, or put in any dedicated recycling container 42 gallons or less (make sure container is covered, marked with recycling stickers on both sides and weighs less than 50 lbs. when full). Please do not put recycling out in plastic bags. All cardboard boxes must be flattened and tied into bundles.

Include

  • Telephone books
  • Junk mail
  • School paper, office paper or other scrap paper
  • Unsoiled newspapers, magazines, penny-savers
  • Gift boxes
  • Cereal boxes (Remove plastic liner)
  • Detergent, macaroni and shoe boxes (Remove plastic windows, if any, from the boxes)
  • Corrugated shipping and packing boxes.

Exclude

  • Tissues
  • Soiled paper
  • Paper towels
  • Milk, juice and egg cartons
  • All wax coated cardboard
  • Books,
  • Soiled cardboard food boxes

Place these items with your regular garbage.

Additional Recycling Information:

  • “Back To Basics” dual stream recycling collection
  • Recycling containers and decals
  • Recycling contamination or “when in doubt throw it out”
